# The Three Communication Paths

Every Pod connection is one of three ‚Äî routed differently.

## 1 ¬∑ Pod ‚Üí Pod

- **Same node** ‚Äî host bridges `veth`‚Üí`veth`. No overlay/proxy.
- **Diff node** ‚Äî CNI routes: Calico BGP (L3 hop) / Flannel VXLAN (UDP encap).
- **No NAT** ‚Äî source IP preserved.

## 2 ¬∑ Pod ‚Üí Service

> DNS ‚Üí ClusterIP ‚Üí **kube-proxy DNATs** to a random Pod. Dest sees the **client's IP** (VIP is virtual).

## 3 ¬∑ Pod ‚Üí External

> Pod IP not public ‚Üí host **source-NATs** to node IP. External sees the **node's IP**. (Pod IP ‚Üí `externalTrafficPolicy: Local` / egress gw / mesh.)

```
pod‚Üípod : A ‚Üí B (direct)
pod‚Üísvc : A ‚Üí VIP ‚Üí kube-proxy DNAT ‚Üí pod
pod‚Üíext : A ‚Üí node (SNAT) ‚Üí internet
```

> *"Why unreachable?" = which path, which layer.*
